Meanwhile have done a fellowship in the Postgraduate Program in Pediatric Nutrition at Boston University School of Medicine. He is a member of the National Neonatology Forum (NNF) and the Indian Academy of Pediatrics (IAP). His areas of expertise include handling level 3 NICU care, well experienced in managing all neonatal problems including extremely preterm and low birth weight babies, babies requiring advanced ventilation, Nitric oxide, Cooling Therapy, also caring for babies requiring surgical intervention. Also hailed for expertise in General Pediatrics, Vaccinations, Nutrition, Growth and Development.
